#: ../../reference/configuration/twig.rst:108
msgid ""
"This is the controller that is activated after an exception is thrown "
"anywhere in your application. The default controller "
"(:class:`Symfony\\\\Bundle\\\\TwigBundle\\\\Controller\\\\ExceptionController`)"
" is what's responsible for rendering specific templates under different "
"error conditions (see :doc:`/cookbook/controller/error_pages`). Modifying "
"this option is advanced. If you need to customize an error page you should "
"use the previous link. If you need to perform some behavior on an exception,"
" you should add a listener to the ``kernel.exception`` event (see :ref:`dic-"
"tags-kernel-event-listener`)."
